narratives.question_text: Were the resources available to you - library, fabrication labs, classroom, software, desk space, etc. adequate for the fulfillment of the assigned work?  If not, please make suggestions.
comments: Yes, they were available. I had to heavily utilize Borrow Direct and the Interlibrary Loan because the HAAS is absolutely terrible in only permitting the loan of a single book for a single day.
The administration showed extraordinary support in our use of the drawing studio for our final project.
Yes, most of the books needed for the subject were in the library.
Haas Library is a joke. It is the most useless resource YSOA has to offer. The lending policies are asinine.
